		<div id="comment_body_64751830"><p>Telephone companies<br>* one-to-one<br>* used to have Yellow Pages to lookup keywords, only included legally established businesses<br>* collaborate with the authorities: wiretapping, owner name, list of contacts, list of text messages, location data.</p><p>Telegram<br>* group chats<br>* find a group chat by keyword; unfiltered, anything you might think of<br>* does not collaborate with the authorities</p><p>It's the "does not collaborate" that make them into problems.</p><p>Telegram is closer to Facebook groups than to telephone. But Meta has functio<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64751830">

</div>
